snippet.textDisplay:
1sr I payed my hard earned money to watch "Joker" while it remained in the theatre for months, *(its actually still playing in Florida) I am guessing about 20 times when i finally just pulled out my iphone 11 and bootlegged a copy so i could enjoy one of the best performances by any actor I have ever seen, what is so powerful about this movie is each and every time I watch it, I see something new, I feel something different, its the movie that I can watch over and over and over again and it never gets old, now i have a clean copy and watch it each night as i fall alseep, am i crazy or was the performance mind blowing, lets all remember there was a script a director and other actors that brought together what could be called the perfect storm; but let me remind you that movies are shot one scene @ a time, there is a scene they study there lines they shoot it, its good they move on maybe on only one take, other scenes maybe its 40 takes to get to the next scene, take that thought and know that JP, occupies 93% of every scene shot in the movie, JP is the real reason it is the highest grossing R film of all time beating out all the Matrix, the Deadpool and any other move R ever made and will hold that title for a long time, JP your performance moved you up to my favorite actor pushing Leo D, down too 2nd place, JP, what an amazing enlightened man you are and I really felt your speech, you have already proven too the world that you can do anything you put your mind body and spirit into, so now JP, look around and you will find a plethora off ways to spark the fire of chance in the world we live in, start with one that makes you think is the hardest and focus your energy on that one and you will be the driving force behind the solution, after hearing your speech I believe its time for you to take off your acting hat and put on your thinking cap, show us what you can do with the amazing gifts you possess.




when ever your ready to really make a difference in this world, I will hear from you and see from you what you already know your are going too do.




after hearing your speech I had reminiscent thought that I was listening to Prince*rest in peace....








and for all those other then JP, you might like too know, JP was asked : So what was it like working with Robert D., and JP said the realest shit I ever heard, I really do not know, I was too busy in my character we never spoke once outside off our shots in scenes together, JP is not a :FAN BOY, and was so into his role he was unable to have a conversation with Robert D. or anyone for that matter, and thats why he won the best actor oscor, once the first scene was shot he was the joker to the final cut, and thats what real actors do.....






I am surprised he was able to move back to JP from Joker so fast, Sissy S. won her Oscar for a coal miners daughter and was so into the role she admitted it took her 2 years to stop talking like Loretta Lynn, think about that.
